Sri Lanka Private Credit Growth Rise Not Alarming, Cabraal Says

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e   a n d   A s a n t h a   S i r i m a n n e
-- 
2011-03-28T07:04:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/sri-lanka-private-credit-growth-rise-not-alarming-cabraal-says.html
Sri Lankan private sector’s
expanding credit growth “is not alarming” even as it is being
monitored by the island’s authorities, the central bank’s
Governor Ajith Nivard Cabraal said by telephone today.  Personal and corporate credit in  Sri Lanka  grew 28.1
percent in January from a year earlier after expanding 25.1
percent in December, the central bank said on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in Colombo at 
 anushao@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hari Govind at 
 hgovind@bloomberg.net  